<blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="margin:0 0 0 .8ex;border-left:1px #ccc solid;padding-left:1ex">Hello CrisisMappers,<br><br>A friend of mine is running the <font face="arial,helvetica,sans-serif"> the <a href="http://centennial.rockefellerfoundation.org/innovators" target="_blank"><span>Rockefeller</span> Foundation&#39;s Next Century Innovators Award</a>
 competition, which is now open for</font><font face="arial,helvetica,sans-serif"><font face="arial,helvetica,sans-serif"><font face="arial,helvetica,sans-serif"> you to <a href="http://centennial.rockefellerfoundation.org/innovators/nominate" target="_blank">nominate your favorite innovators</a>
 (individuals or organizations, including yourself if you like.) for the
 Next 
Century Innovators Award</font>. </font>Below is my friend&#39;s short 
description of what they&#39;re looking for. Good luck!<br>
<br></font><font face="arial,helvetica,sans-serif">Thanks,<br></font><font face="arial,helvetica,sans-serif">JD<br></font><div><br>--------------<br></div><div>The <font face="arial,helvetica,sans-serif"><font face="arial,helvetica,sans-serif"> Next 
Century Innovators Award</font></font></div><br><div><span style="line-height:115%;font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,&quot;serif&quot;"><font face="arial,helvetica,sans-serif">In the <span>Rockefeller</span> Foundation’s centennial year, we plan to highlight 100
innovators globally, and then 3 of them, including one organization dedicated to youth, will receive an
award at our Innovation Forum in May 2013, and will additionally be eligible to
apply for a grant. Two of the winners will be chosen by <span>Rockefeller</span> Foundation,
and an additional three finalists will be subject to a crowdsourced vote to determine
the final award. </font></span></div><div><font face="arial,helvetica,sans-serif"> </font></div><font face="arial,helvetica,sans-serif">We&#39;re
 looking for innovations that have already demonstrated impact, but 
still have potential to catalyze systemic change.  <span>Rockefeller</span>&#39;s 
description of innovation follows, and gives a sense of 
the types of innovation that are appropriate.  Descriptions of some of 
last year&#39;s winners are also on the site.<br><br></font><span>Rockefeller</span>&#39;s description of innovation: &quot;An innovation is a break from previous practice. It occurs
when different points of view or existing elements are framed, imagined or
combined in new ways. Innovation succeeds when it creates new pathways for
solving entrenched social problems, resulting in lasting change within the
systems that affect poor and vulnerable populations.&quot;<br><br><br><br clear="all">JD Godchaux<br>Executive Director<br><span><br>NiJeL - Data. Mapping. Community Impact.<div><br>
